Storms wreak havoc in central China's Hunan
2012-05-11 06:24:37 GMT
More than 1.2 million people in Hunan province have been affected by storms and hail that have wreaked havoc since Tuesday, local flood control officials said Thursday.A total of 55 warnings were issued for inclement weather between Tuesday and Thursday morning, including 34 rain warnings, five hail warnings, six warnings for high winds and ten for thunderstorms, according to the Hunan provincial meteorological center.  
